title.narrative: USAID Balkan Media Assistance Program (BMAP) II - CRIF

description.narrative: (Bosnia and Herzegovina): Digital attacks from both domestic and external forces have increasingly been infringing on media and compromising the security of journalists in Western Balkan countries, particularly Serbia, Bosnia and Herzegovina, and Montenegro. Despite the risks, most journalists in these countries do little to protect their devices and accounts against the risk of digital attack or intrusion. There are few practical digital security resources available online in Balkan languages. USAID will add $250,000 of FY 19 to BMAP increase the digital security of key partners of the project. BMAP will work on the development of educational content on digital security for Balkansmedia.org (project's online platform for sharing the content between media partners), digital security audits for at-risk BMAP media partners, digital security training and risk reduction grants for digital security equipment and software. One hundred percent of funding of these activities will address CAATSA Goal 5 by building the capacity of media and other nongovernmental organizations to counter the influence and propaganda of the Russian Federation, to combat corruption, prioritize access to truthful information, and operate freely. It also advances EUR Joint Regional Strategy Goals 3.1 and 4.1 by strengthening independent media and civil society.. .

Objectives for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kosovo, Macedonia, Montenegro, and Serbia: USAID’s Balkan Media Assistance Program is making media practitioners in Bosnia and Herzegovina, Kosovo, Macedonia, Montenegro, and Serbia more competitive in the local and regional marketplace and strengthening the sustainability of independent media in the region
